From: Dongdong Deng <dongdong.deng@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Sep 2010 06:40:18 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 24/31] kgdboe: check kgdboe whether initialized or not when
 cleanup kgdboe

If the kgdboe didn't be initialized, the cleanup_kgdboe() should
do nothing.

Signed-off-by: Dongdong Deng <dongdong.deng@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Jason Wessel <jason.wessel@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/kgdboe.c |    4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/kgdboe.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/kgdboe.c
index 1e13b70..a5f24bc 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/kgdboe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/kgdboe.c
@@ -212,9 +212,11 @@ static int init_kgdboe(void)
 
 static void cleanup_kgdboe(void)
 {
+	if (configured != 2)
+		return;
 	netpoll_cleanup(&np);
-	configured = 0;
 	kgdb_unregister_io_module(&local_kgdb_io_ops);
+	configured = 0;
 }
 
 static int param_set_kgdboe_var(const char *kmessage, struct kernel_param *kp)
